&lt;p&gt;According to McKinsey, &lt;a href="https://www.mckinsey.com/capabilities/growth-marketing-and-sales/our-insights/new-front-door-to-the-internet-winning-in-the-age-of-ai-search"&gt;50% of consumers&lt;/a&gt; now use AI-powered search, and more than 70% rely on it to ask questions and gather information. This shift in search behavior means SEO leaders must evolve. Modern workflows need to incorporate &lt;a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/answer-engine-optimization"&gt;Answer Engine Optimization (AEO)&lt;/a&gt; strategies so brands can not only rank on page one of Google, but also gain visibility inside AI-generated answers across platforms like Google AI Overviews, ChatGPT, and Perplexity.&lt;/p&gt;  
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class="cta_button" href="https://www.hubspot.com/cs/ci/?pg=d4233c10-60b6-46d7-9852-c71dde8507b6&amp;amp;pid=53&amp;amp;ecid=&amp;amp;hseid=&amp;amp;hsic="&gt;&lt;img class="hs-cta-img " style="height: auto !important; width: auto !important; max-width: 100% !important;border-width: 0px; /*hs-extra-styles*/; margin: 0 auto; display: block; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px" alt="Free AEO Grader: See Your Brand's Visibility in Answer Engines [Free Tool]" height="58" width="679" src="https://no-cache.hubspot.com/cta/default/53/d4233c10-60b6-46d7-9852-c71dde8507b6.png" align="middle"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;This means marketing leaders need to know what’s going on with their brand in AI search. How are AI tools referring to it, citing it, and in relation to what search queries are brands showing up?&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Enter Profound and Peec AI. These AI Visibility tools are designed to help marketing teams monitor, measure, and improve their &lt;a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/best-content-for-sge"&gt;content for search generative experiences (SGE)&lt;/a&gt; while tracking how AI answer engines represent their brand.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;As AEO becomes a strategic priority, marketers are evaluating Profound AI vs. Peec AI for AEO and seeking a clear comparison between the two. This guide breaks down what each platform offers, how they differ, and which solution best supports a team’s strategy.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Table of Contents&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#why-marketers-should-consider-profound-and-peec-for-aeo"&gt;Why Marketers Should Consider Profound and Peec for AEO&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#profound-vs-peec-ai-for-aeo-comparison-at-a-glance"&gt;Profound vs. Peec AI for AEO: Comparison at a Glance&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#profound-vs-peec-compared"&gt;Profound vs. Peec Compared&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#which-should-you-choose-for-aeo-profound-or-peec"&gt;Which should you choose for AEO, Profound or Peec?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#frequently-asked-questions-about-profound-vs-peec-ai-for-aeo"&gt;Frequently Asked Questions About Profound vs. Peec AI for AEO&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#the-right-aeo-platform-for-sustainable-growth"&gt;The Right AEO Platform for Sustainable Growth&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt; 
&lt;h2&gt;Why Marketers Should Consider Profound and Peec for AEO&lt;/h2&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;As AI-powered answer engines reshape how people discover information, marketers need new ways to measure and influence brand visibility beyond traditional search. Platforms like &lt;strong&gt;Peec AI&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Profound AI&lt;/strong&gt; sit at the center of this shift. Both are designed for Answer Engine Optimization (AEO), helping teams understand how their brand appears inside AI-generated responses across tools like ChatGPT, Claude, and Perplexity.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;At a high level, they solve similar problems — tracking AI mentions, citations, and visibility — but they differ in depth, complexity, and intended use cases.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Peec AI&lt;/strong&gt; focuses on clarity and accessibility. It offers straightforward visibility tracking, sentiment analysis, and competitive benchmarking. It’s well-suited for teams that want quick insights without heavy implementation. The tradeoff is that it may lack some of the deeper integrations and advanced workflow capabilities larger organizations need.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Profound AI&lt;/strong&gt;, by contrast, is built for scale and actionability. It combines visibility tracking with deeper analytics, integrations, and optimization workflows. With Profound, enterprise teams can connect AI presence directly to content strategy and business outcomes. However, that added power can come with more complexity and a steeper learning curve.&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Marketers should consider tools like Peec AI or Profound AI because AI answer engines are increasingly shaping what customers see and trust, and these platforms reveal whether — and how — a brand appears in those responses. Both platforms help marketers understand and optimize how their brand shows up in AI responses, an increasingly important part of modern search visibility as AI answers replace traditional blue links.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;h3&gt;Peec AI&lt;/h3&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://53.fs1.hubspotusercontent-na1.net/hubfs/53/profound-vs-peec-ai-for-aeo-2-20260710-7815836.webp" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block; width: 450px; height: auto; max-width: 100%;" alt="profound ai vs peec: Screenshot shows Peec AI analysis open with charts, competitor analysis, and listed domains."&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p style="text-align: center; font-size: 12px;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://peec.ai/"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Source&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://peec.ai/"&gt;Peec AI&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; is an AI visibility and search analytics platform focused on helping teams quickly understand how their brand appears across AI answer engines. It tracks core AEO metrics like:&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Brand mentions and citations.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Sentiment in AI-generated responses.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Competitive visibility across models and regions.&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Where Peec stands out is in its simplicity and speed to insight. The platform surfaces clear, digestible data that makes it easy to benchmark performance and spot gaps without requiring heavy setup or technical integration. This makes it a strong fit for:&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Marketing teams new to AEO.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Companies prioritizing fast reporting and competitive insights.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Teams that want visibility without complex workflows.&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;The tradeoff is that Peec is more focused on measurement than activation. While it helps marketers and SEO professionals understand how their brand shows up, it offers fewer built-in tools for turning those insights into execution across content and workflows.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;h3&gt;Profound&lt;/h3&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://53.fs1.hubspotusercontent-na1.net/hubfs/53/profound-vs-peec-ai-for-aeo-3-20260710-6319271.webp" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block; width: 450px; height: auto; max-width: 100%;" alt="profound ai vs peec: Screenshot shows Profound AI analysis open with charts, brand visibility graphs, and listed domains."&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p style="text-align: center; font-size: 12px;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.tryprofound.com/features/answer-engine-insights"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Source&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.tryprofound.com/"&gt;Profound AI&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; is an enterprise-grade AEO platform designed to measure AI visibility and help teams actively improve it. Profound’s key strength is its actionability at scale. Like Peec, it tracks mentions, citations, and presence across AI systems. But, th...

&lt;p&gt;Organic search still delivers some of the strongest returns in marketing, and the right content optimization tools make it easier to capture.&lt;/p&gt;  
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class="cta_button" href="https://www.hubspot.com/cs/ci/?pg=b9960dd8-68b8-4caa-8a08-d3f7b7c3406e&amp;amp;pid=53&amp;amp;ecid=&amp;amp;hseid=&amp;amp;hsic="&gt;&lt;img class="hs-cta-img " style="height: auto !important; width: auto !important; max-width: 100% !important;border-width: 0px; /*hs-extra-styles*/; margin: 0 auto; display: block; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px" alt="Get Started with HubSpot's Marketing Software for Free" height="60" width="502" src="https://no-cache.hubspot.com/cta/default/53/b9960dd8-68b8-4caa-8a08-d3f7b7c3406e.png" align="middle"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;But in 2026, the stakes are higher than they used to be. AI search engines like Google AI Overviews, Perplexity, and ChatGPT are now a standard part of the buyer research process, and they don’t select sources the same way traditional search does. Marketing teams that optimize only for Google rankings often find themselves invisible in AI-generated answers — and being invisible in AI answers means invisible to buyers.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;This guide covers the best content optimization tools available in 2026, organized by use case. Whether the goal is to build a content stack from scratch or to fill gaps in an existing &lt;a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/content-optimization"&gt;content optimization workflow&lt;/a&gt;, this guide breaks down what each tool does and who it’s best for.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Table of Contents&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#types-of-content-optimization-tools"&gt;Types of Content Optimization Tools&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#the-best-content-optimization-tools-by-use-case"&gt;The Best Content Optimization Tools by Use Case&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#frequently-asked-questions-about-content-optimization-tools"&gt;Frequently Asked Questions About Content Optimization Tools&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt; 
&lt;h2&gt;Types of Content Optimization Tools&lt;/h2&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Content optimization tools improve content quality, search visibility, and conversion performance. Plenty of content and &lt;a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/seo-analysis-tools"&gt;SEO analysis tools&lt;/a&gt; are on the market, and many of them cover a wide range of functions.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Before we get into specific recommendations for AI content optimization tools, here’s a breakdown of the major categories:&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;On-page optimization and content scoring tools&lt;/strong&gt; analyze published or draft content against top-ranking pages, flagging keyword gaps, structural issues, and readability problems.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research, brief creation, and content-writing accelerators&lt;/strong&gt; help marketing teams plan and draft faster, using AI to generate outlines, briefs, and first drafts grounded in keyword and intent data.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal linking and site structure tools&lt;/strong&gt; identify opportunities to strengthen semantic relationships between pages and improve crawlability.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experimentation and content QA tools&lt;/strong&gt; enable content teams to test content variations and audit existing pages for technical or structural issues before publishing or republishing.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance reporting and strategy tools&lt;/strong&gt; track how content performs across rankings, traffic, engagement, and increasingly, AI visibility — including whether a brand appears in AI-generated answers.&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HubSpot pro tip:&lt;/strong&gt; As AI visibility becomes a standard reporting requirement, tools that track it become more important. &lt;a href="https://www.hubspot.com/products/aeo"&gt;HubSpot AEO&lt;/a&gt; shows where a brand appears in AI-generated answers across ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Gemini — and connects that data to the same CRM where the team is already tracking leads and pipeline.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Featured Resource:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/website/best-cms-for-seo"&gt;9 SEO-friendly CMS options&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt; 
&lt;h2&gt;The Best Content Optimization Tools by Use Case&lt;/h2&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;The most effective content stacks combine &lt;a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/seo"&gt;SEO optimization&lt;/a&gt; software with specialized tools for research, AI visibility, and reporting. The breakdowns below are organized by category, covering what each tool does, who it’s best for, and how it fits into a content stack.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;h3&gt;On-Page Optimization and Content Scoring&lt;/h3&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;These tools &lt;a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/content-scoring"&gt;analyze and score content&lt;/a&gt; against top-ranking competitors, surfacing specific recommendations to close gaps. Most use &lt;a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/what-is-latent-semantic-indexing-why-does-it-matter-for-your-seo-strategy"&gt;NLP and semantic analysis&lt;/a&gt; rather than simple keyword density.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.hubspot.com/products/marketing/seo"&gt;HubSpot SEO Marketing Software&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://53.fs1.hubspotusercontent-na1.net/hub/53/hubfs/content%20optimization%20tools%2c%20HubSpot%20SEO.webp?width=650&amp;amp;height=413&amp;amp;name=content%20optimization%20tools%2c%20HubSpot%20SEO.webp" width="650" height="413" alt="content optimization tools, HubSpot SEO" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block; width: 650px; height: auto; max-width: 100%;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;HubSpot’s SEO Marketing Software is built into Marketing Hub and provides teams with a centralized view of SEO performance, on-page recommendations, and topic cluster structure. It’s all connected to the same CRM data that powers the rest of HubSpot’s platform.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Unlike standalone SEO tools, HubSpot’s SEO recommendations are tied directly to a brand’s actual content and pages. Teams can see which pages need optimization, act on those recommendations within the same platform, and track the downstream impact on traffic and leads without switching between tools or manually stitching together data.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What I like: &lt;/strong&gt;The biggest advantage isn’t the recommendations themselves (which are solid) — it’s that they’re connected to real pipeline data. When a content team can show that improving a cluster of pages drove a measurable increase in marketing-qualified lead (MQL) volume, securing executive buy-in for SEO investment becomes much easier.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Features&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;On-page SEO recommendations with step-by-step guidance&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Topic cluster visualization and internal linking suggestions&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Page-level performance data connected to CRM and contact records&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;SEO analysis tied to real traffic, leads, and revenue attribution&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Best for:&lt;/strong&gt; Marketing teams already on HubSpot who want integrated SEO visibility without managing a separate tool. Ideal for mid-market and enterprise teams that need to report on content ROI across the full funnel.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pro tip:&lt;/strong&gt; Teams on Marketing Hub Professional or Enterprise can add AEO through the HubSpot for Marketers bundle, keeping SEO and AI search visibility in one platform.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What the experts say&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;a ...

&lt;p&gt;Wholesale businesses require more than a generic customer relationship management (CRM) system. A CRM for wholesalers must support account-specific pricing, large product catalogs, repeat orders, and sales workflows that integrate with inventory and fulfillment systems. When these processes are disconnected, quoting slows, errors increase, and revenue opportunities are harder to capture.&lt;/p&gt;  
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class="cta_button" href="https://www.hubspot.com/cs/ci/?pg=b173b371-487a-4b24-8d8d-508e4cff3779&amp;amp;pid=53&amp;amp;ecid=&amp;amp;hseid=&amp;amp;hsic="&gt;&lt;img class="hs-cta-img " style="height: auto !important; width: auto !important; max-width: 100% !important;border-width: 0px; /*hs-extra-styles*/; margin: 0 auto; display: block; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px" alt="Learn more about why HubSpot's CRM platform has all the tools you need to grow  better." height="58" width="802" src="https://no-cache.hubspot.com/cta/default/53/b173b371-487a-4b24-8d8d-508e4cff3779.png" align="middle"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;The best CRM for wholesale distributors connects customer data with pricing logic, order workflows, and inventory visibility. This setup allows sales teams to move from quote to order without switching systems, while giving operations leaders accurate pipeline insight and enabling field reps to work effectively from mobile devices.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;This guide compares the best CRM software for wholesalers in 2026. The guide evaluates each platform based on wholesale-specific requirements like enterprise resource planning (ERP) and inventory integration, mobile field sales capabilities, pricing flexibility, and total cost of ownership.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Table of Contents&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#what-is-a-crm-for-wholesalers"&gt;What is a CRM for wholesalers?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#best-crms-for-wholesalers-at-a-glance"&gt;Best CRMs for Wholesalers at a Glance&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#best-crm-software-for-wholesalers"&gt;Best CRM Software for Wholesalers&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#benefits-of-crm-software-for-wholesalers"&gt;Benefits of CRM Software for Wholesalers&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#8-important-features-for-a-wholesale-crm"&gt;8 Important Features for a Wholesale CRM&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#how-to-choose-a-crm-for-wholesalers-step-by-step"&gt;How to Choose a CRM for Wholesalers (Step-by-Step)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#frequently-asked-questions"&gt;Frequently Asked Questions About CRMs for Wholesalers&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt; 
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is a CRM for wholesalers?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;A CRM for wholesalers is a customer relationship management system designed to support B2B distribution workflows, including account-specific pricing, bulk ordering, and sales processes integrated with inventory and fulfillment systems. It helps wholesale teams manage accounts, generate accurate quotes, and move orders forward without relying on disconnected tools.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Wholesale CRM software supports customer-specific pricing and tiered price lists, allowing distributors to apply contract pricing, volume discounts, and negotiated terms at the account level. It also connects sales workflows to inventory and order status data, typically through integrations with ERP systems.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;In practice, the CRM system manages accounts, contacts, deals, and sales activity, while the ERP system manages inventory, purchasing, and fulfillment. This separation allows wholesale teams to maintain accurate operational data while giving sales teams the context they need to quote and sell efficiently. Many of these requirements overlap with those in &lt;a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/best-crm-for-manufacturing"&gt;manufacturing environments&lt;/a&gt;, where CRM systems also connect sales activity to production and fulfillment processes.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wholesaler CRM vs. Standard CRM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Wholesale distribution introduces requirements that standard CRMs do not fully support without additional configuration or integrations. These differences affect how teams price, sell, and fulfill orders.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tiered and contract pricing:&lt;/strong&gt; Wholesale CRM software supports account-specific price lists, volume discounts, and negotiated terms. Standard CRMs typically require integrations or customization to handle this level of pricing complexity.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Large product catalogs and stock-keeping units (SKUs):&lt;/strong&gt; Wholesale teams manage extensive product catalogs with multiple variations. Standard CRMs offer basic product records but often rely on external systems for full catalog management.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inventory visibility during sales:&lt;/strong&gt; Wholesale sales teams need access to stock availability when building quotes. Standard CRMs depend on ERP or inventory integrations to provide this information.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Multi-location inventory:&lt;/strong&gt; Wholesale distributors often sell across warehouses, branches, or regions. Standard CRMs typically require ERP or inventory integrations to display location-specific stock availability during quoting.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Repeat ordering workflows:&lt;/strong&gt; Wholesale operations rely on frequent reorders and order history. Standard CRMs typically require workflows or integrations to support repeat-order processes.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Electronic data interchange (EDI) and partner requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Many wholesalers exchange purchase orders, invoices, and shipping notices via EDI. Standard CRMs rarely support EDI without third-party tools.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Territory and field sales coverage:&lt;/strong&gt; Wholesale sales teams often operate on a regional, account-ownership, or product-line basis. While standard CRMs support territories, wholesalers typically require more structured coverage models tied to distribution operations.&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt; 
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Best CRMs for Wholesalers at a Glance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Wholesale CRM requirements often overlap with adjacent industries like retail, but differ in pricing models, order volume, and account structure. See this guide to the &lt;a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/best-crm-for-retail"&gt;best CRMs for retail&lt;/a&gt; for a comparison of customer-focused sales environments.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt; 
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Best CRM Software for Wholesalers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;The right CRM helps wholesale teams reduce quoting delays, connect sales activity with inventory data, and give reps clearer account visibility. The six CRM platforms below address different wholesale needs, from field sales and stock-aware quoting to enterprise forecasting and ERP connectivity.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.hubspot.com/crm/"&gt;HubSpot Smart CRM&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt; 
